  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" K. Mangayarkarasi & Anr. versus N.J. Sundaresan & Anr. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_5_1199_1220','2025INSC687'); ><font size='4'> <strong>K. MANGAYARKARASI & ANR.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>N.J. SUNDARESAN & ANR. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 5 S.C.R. 1199</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 687</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010005862025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.B. PARDIWALA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, R MAHADEVAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Can a trademark infringement suit be referred to arbitration if the defendant questions its maintainability on the ground of existence of an arbitration agreement between the parties and seeks a reference under Section 8 of the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, Act, 1996 &ndash; s.8 &ndash; Not all trademark disputes are non-arbitrable; those concerning contractual rights can be arbitrated &ndash; Petitioners filed a commercial suit against Respondents seeking permanent injunction in relation to trademark &ldquo;SRI ANGANNAN BIRIYANI HOTEL/ABM<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 09-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> SPECIAL LEAVE PETITION (CIVIL) No. 13012/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_5_1199_1220','2025INSC687','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='co